<item>
            <title>[PIG-4736] Removing empty keys in UDFContext broke one LoadFunc</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-4736</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-4697&quot; title=&quot;Serialize relevant part of the udfcontext per vertex to reduce payload size&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PIG-4697&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PIG-4697&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; separated UDFContext specific to each vertex. But it also had an optimization to remove empty keys. That broke one user LoadFunc which was keeping the UDFContext Properties as a local variable and serializing in setLocation only if getSchema() was called. Even if UDFContext.isFrontend() logic was used it would have worked.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
